name: r-caretensemble
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2.0.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-caretensemble
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/caretEnsemble_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/caretEnsemble/caretEnsemble_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7e595e604ce2d9d32afbc5404e6fcbcd7f80e687316e9ca3303aca3e44c3ef88

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-caret
    - r-data.table
    - r-digest
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-gridextra
    - r-lattice
    - r-pbapply
    - r-plyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-caret
    - r-data.table
    - r-digest
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-gridextra
    - r-lattice
    - r-pbapply
    - r-plyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('caretEnsemble')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('caretEnsemble')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/zachmayer/caretEnsemble
  license: MIT
  summary: 'Functions for creating ensembles of caret models: caretList() and caretStack().  caretList()
    is a convenience function for fitting multiple caret::train() models to the same
    dataset. caretStack() will make linear or non-linear combinations of these models,
    using a caret::train() model as a meta-model, and caretEnsemble() will make a robust
    linear combination of models using a GLM.'
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Encoding: UTF-8

# URL: https://github.com/zachmayer/caretEnsemble
